Record Class TileData

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
it.polimi.it.galaxytrucker.model.componenttiles.TileData
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public record TileData(int rotation, String type, TileEdge top, TileEdge right, TileEdge bottom, TileEdge left, String graphicPath, int batteryCharge, List<String> crewmates, List<Color> cargo, int capacity, String alienSupport) extends Record implements Serializable
Represents the essential data of a game tile, used for serialization and deserialization. This record captures the state of a ComponentTile in a simplified format.

The fields of this record include:

  • rotation: The rotation of the tile in 90° increments (0, 1, 2, 3).
  • type: The string representation of the tile's type (e.g., "BatteryComponent", "CentralCabin").
  • top: The TileEdge configuration for the top side of the tile.
  • right: The TileEdge configuration for the right side of the tile.
  • bottom: The TileEdge configuration for the bottom side of the tile.
  • left: The TileEdge configuration for the left side of the tile.
  • graphicPath: The file path to the graphic representation of the tile.
  • batteryCharge: The current battery charge of the tile. Applicable only for "BatteryComponent" tiles; otherwise, it is 0.
  • crewmates: A list of strings representing the types of crewmates on the tile. Applicable for "CentralCabin" and "CabinModule" tiles; otherwise, it is an empty list. Crewmates are represented as "HUMAN" or the uppercase string of the alien type ("PURPLE", "BROWN").
  • cargo: A list of Color enums representing the colors of cargo on the tile. Applicable for "CargoHold" and "SpecialCargoHold" tiles; otherwise, it is an empty list.
  • capacity: The maximum amount of cargo the component can contain. Applicable for "CargoHold" and "SpecialCargoHold" tiles; otherwise, it is 0.

      public TileData(int rotation, String type, TileEdge top, TileEdge right, TileEdge bottom, TileEdge left, String graphicPath, int batteryCharge, List<String> crewmates, List<Color> cargo, int capacity, String alienSupport)
      Constructs a TileData record. This constructor is annotated with JsonCreator to facilitate deserialization from JSON, mapping JSON properties to record components.
      Parameters:
      rotation - The rotation of the tile in 90° increments (0, 1, 2, 3).
      type - The string representation of the tile's type (e.g., "BatteryComponent", "CentralCabin").
      top - The TileEdge configuration for the top side of the tile.
      right - The TileEdge configuration for the right side of the tile.
      bottom - The TileEdge configuration for the bottom side of the tile.
      left - The TileEdge configuration for the left side of the tile.
      graphicPath - The file path to the graphic representation of the tile.
      batteryCharge - The current battery charge of the tile, if applicable (0 otherwise).
      crewmates - A list of strings representing the types of crewmates on the tile ("HUMAN" or "PURPLE"/"BROWN" for aliens).
      cargo - A list of Color enums representing the colors of cargo on the tile.
      capacity - capacity: The maximum amount of cargo the component can contain. Applicable for "CargoHold" and "SpecialCargoHold" tiles; otherwise, it is 0.

  • Method Details

    • createTileDataFromComponentTile

      public static TileData createTileDataFromComponentTile(ComponentTile componentTile)
      Converts a ComponentTile object to a TileData record object. This static factory method extracts relevant data from a ComponentTile and populates a new TileData instance. It handles specific component types (e.g., BatteryComponent, CentralCabin, CargoHold) to correctly extract their unique properties.
      Parameters:
      componentTile - The component to be converted. Can be null.
      Returns:
      The TileData representation of the given component, or null if the input component is null.

    • createTileDataShipFromComponentTileShip

      public static List<List<TileData>> createTileDataShipFromComponentTileShip(List<List<ComponentTile>> ship)
      Converts a matrix (list of lists) of ComponentTile objects to a matrix of TileData objects. This method iterates through the provided ship structure, converting each ComponentTile into its TileData equivalent using createTileDataFromComponentTile(ComponentTile).
      Parameters:
      ship - The matrix of ComponentTiles to be converted. Representing the ship layout.
      Returns:
      A List<List<TileData>> representing the converted ship matrix. Each inner list represents a row of tiles.
